WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.770
There you go.

00:02.803 --> 00:03.804
Oh.

00:03.837 --> 00:05.373
[snickering]

00:08.442 --> 00:09.643
Nice dress, Ryan.

00:09.677 --> 00:12.480
It's not a dress.
It's a kurta.

00:12.513 --> 00:13.581
[laughing]
Okay.

00:13.614 --> 00:15.249
Tonight,
one of our most

00:15.283 --> 00:17.351
ethnic coworkers,
Kelly,

00:17.385 --> 00:20.054
has invited us all
to a Diwali celebration

00:20.088 --> 00:22.090
put on by her community.

00:22.123 --> 00:23.757
What is Diwali,
you may ask?

00:23.791 --> 00:27.395
Well, to have Kelly
explain it,

00:27.428 --> 00:28.629
[high voice]
"It's..."

00:28.662 --> 00:30.664
[gibberish]

00:30.698 --> 00:32.233
"It's so super, fun.

00:32.266 --> 00:34.168
And it's gonna be great."

00:34.202 --> 00:36.337
A lot of gods
with unpronounceable names.

00:36.370 --> 00:38.139
20 minutes later,
you find out

00:38.172 --> 00:40.741
that it's essentially
a Hindu Halloween.

00:40.774 --> 00:42.176
You look so handsome.

00:42.210 --> 00:43.211
You really do.

00:43.244 --> 00:45.213
I love the material.

00:45.246 --> 00:46.314
I know.

00:46.347 --> 00:47.515
How come you didn't
get me one?

00:48.782 --> 00:49.783
I...

00:49.817 --> 00:52.786
[piano rock]

00:52.820 --> 01:00.828
*

01:21.815 --> 01:24.318
Okay, so between
Meredith's minivan,

01:24.352 --> 01:25.753
and if I borrow Bob's Yukon,

01:25.786 --> 01:28.189
that should fit
about 12 people.

01:28.222 --> 01:29.823
I actually might not go.

01:29.857 --> 01:31.559
I'm feeling kind of tired.

01:31.592 --> 01:32.560
Do you wanna make Appletinis

01:32.593 --> 01:33.494
and watch Sex and the City
at my place?

01:33.527 --> 01:37.898
Oh, I don't know.
I haven't decided yet.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.167
I don't get
why you won't go.

01:39.200 --> 01:40.134
Did I do something wrong?

01:40.168 --> 01:41.835
I mean, I thought we
were really close friends.

01:41.869 --> 01:43.837
I just feel kind of tired,
you know.

01:43.871 --> 01:45.139
Maybe you've got mono.

01:45.173 --> 01:46.174
Maybe.

01:46.207 --> 01:47.475
I just...

01:47.508 --> 01:48.776
I don't really have
anyone to go with.

01:48.809 --> 01:50.511
Well, go with Dwight.

01:50.544 --> 01:52.146
He's single too right?

01:52.180 --> 01:53.314
Yeah, totally single.

01:53.347 --> 01:55.616
100% available.

01:55.649 --> 01:58.786
Are you guys going to this
Indian thing tonight?

01:58.819 --> 02:02.556
I don't know.
Who's, uh, who's going?

02:02.590 --> 02:05.859
Ohh...you mean, like,
is Pam going?

02:05.893 --> 02:08.229
Don't go.
They eat monkey brains.

02:08.262 --> 02:10.164
(Michael)
Hey, hey, hey, stop that.

02:10.198 --> 02:11.232
That is offensive.

02:11.265 --> 02:13.934
Indians do not
eat monkey brains.

02:13.967 --> 02:15.736
And if they do...

02:15.769 --> 02:17.671
sign me up.

02:17.705 --> 02:19.607
Because I am sure
that they are very tasty.

02:19.640 --> 02:22.410
And nutritional.

02:23.811 --> 02:26.747
It's important
that this company

02:26.780 --> 02:29.750
celebrates its diversity.

02:29.783 --> 02:31.819
And you know what, Stanley?

02:31.852 --> 02:34.455
Come Kwanzaa time,
I have got you covered, baby.

02:34.488 --> 02:36.257
I don't celebrate
Kwanzaa.

02:36.290 --> 02:37.825
Wha--really?

02:37.858 --> 02:39.793
You should.
It's fun.

02:39.827 --> 02:43.397
I love the people here.

02:43.431 --> 02:47.935
And if there was one thing
I don't really care for,

02:47.968 --> 02:51.839
is that they can be
terribly, terribly ignorant

02:51.872 --> 02:53.707
about other cultures.

02:53.741 --> 02:55.976
And I don't want them
embarrassing me

02:56.009 --> 02:58.612
in front
of my girlfriend Carol.

02:58.646 --> 03:02.350
Diwali is a very
important holiday

03:02.383 --> 03:03.517
for the Hindus.

03:03.551 --> 03:05.253
But, frankly,
I'm a little appalled

03:05.286 --> 03:09.357
that none of you know very much
about Indian culture.

03:09.390 --> 03:11.859
So with out further adieu,
Kelly!

03:11.892 --> 03:14.962
You are on.

03:14.995 --> 03:17.431
Um, Diwali is awesome.

03:17.465 --> 03:18.732
And there's food,

03:18.766 --> 03:20.568
and there's gonna be dancing.

03:20.601 --> 03:22.703
And, oh,
I got the raddest outfit.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.705
It has sparkles--
Kelly...

03:24.738 --> 03:26.974
Um, why don't you tell us
a little bit about

03:27.007 --> 03:29.577
the origins of the holiday?

03:29.610 --> 03:32.913
Oh, um, I don't know.
It's really old, I think.

03:32.946 --> 03:34.948
How many gods
do you have?

03:34.982 --> 03:36.984
Like hundreds, I think.
Maybe more than that.

03:37.017 --> 03:39.019
And that blue, busty gal--
what's her story?

03:39.052 --> 03:40.554
(Kevin)
She looks like Pam

03:40.588 --> 03:41.922
from the neck down.

03:41.955 --> 03:42.923
(Dwight)
Pam wishes.

03:42.956 --> 03:44.858
[laughter]

03:44.892 --> 03:46.660
Kelly, I'll take this one.

03:46.694 --> 03:49.930
Diwali is a celebration
of the coronation god king Rama

03:49.963 --> 03:52.400
after his epic battle
with Ravena,

03:52.433 --> 03:53.634
the demon king of Lanka.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.669
It symbolizes the battle
between good and evil.

03:55.703 --> 03:57.438
All right, all right.
This isn't Lord of the Rings.

03:57.471 --> 03:59.239
Hey, Polly.

04:01.709 --> 04:02.843
Oops, sorry.

04:02.876 --> 04:04.445
Sorry.

04:04.478 --> 04:07.047
I started biking to work.
Josh does it.

04:07.080 --> 04:09.750
And he lives a lot
farther away than I do.

04:09.783 --> 04:11.819
And also, it saves gas money.

04:11.852 --> 04:14.922
It keeps me in shape.
Helps the environment.

04:14.955 --> 04:19.993
And now I know it makes me
really sweaty for work.

04:20.027 --> 04:22.863
Nice basket.

04:22.896 --> 04:24.998
Thank you.

04:27.435 --> 04:28.969
Now, a lot of people say

04:29.002 --> 04:31.472
that Kelly
is one in a million.

04:31.505 --> 04:32.806
And that's true,
but it's also not true.

04:32.840 --> 04:34.642
Because, frankly,

04:34.675 --> 04:36.510
there are literally
billions of people

04:36.544 --> 04:38.379
just like Kelly
in the world.

04:38.412 --> 04:41.615
Here are some
famous Indians.

04:44.117 --> 04:47.721
Subrahmanyan Chandrasekhar.

04:47.755 --> 04:51.058
He is a Nobel-Prize-winning
physicist.

04:51.091 --> 04:52.626
Impressive.

04:52.660 --> 04:54.027
Apu, from The Simpsons.

04:54.061 --> 04:56.664
Hilarious Indian.

04:56.697 --> 04:57.898
M. Night Shyamalan.

04:57.931 --> 05:00.100
The Village, Unbreakable,
Sixth Sense.

05:00.133 --> 05:01.969
I see dead people.

05:02.002 --> 05:04.071
Okay!
Spoiler alert.

05:04.104 --> 05:05.773
He was dead
the whole time.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.441
Just stop it!

05:07.475 --> 05:09.009
What's--
Oh, wha--

05:09.042 --> 05:10.110
[laughs]

05:10.143 --> 05:11.612
Where did that come from?

05:15.449 --> 05:16.850
Karen, my chips got stuck

05:16.884 --> 05:18.386
